shoulderright.label: Shoulder Ranges of Motion Figure Table A1 page 596, Corrected with Errata March 2002: AMA Estimated Normal: Flexion (180D), Extension (40D), Abduction (180D), Adduction (30D), External Rotation (90), Internal Rotation (80D). Motion is measured with goniometer and is reported right over left side in Degrees (D).

Actual goniometer measurements of the range of motion are only required for PR-4 (Permanent & Stationary) reports. Visual estimates of the range of motion may be adequate for Doctor's First reports and PR-2 reports.
Manual Muscle Testing
shoulderright.textareatext: Strength Definitions: 5=Complete active range of motion against gravity with full resistance, 4=Complete active range of motion against gravity with some resistance, 3=Complete active range of motion against gravity only, without resistance, 2=Complete active range of motion with gravity eliminated, 1=Evidence of slight contractility; no joint movement, 0=No evidence of contractility
